*[HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__mng_Push_Notificatons|Configuring Push Notifications]

After you install a new instance of Acumatica ERP, most of the product features are disabled. When you sign in to a new Acumatica ERP instance, the only form you can access is the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, which you use to enable the features in accordance with the license you have bought.{br}

Only after you enable the feature all feature-related forms and individual elements appear in Acumatica ERP. If a particular workspace on the UI is associated with a feature or multiple features, that workspace appears only if the feature is enabled. (For example, the ''' Projects''' workspace menu item appears on the main menu only if the ''Project Accounting'' feature is enabled.){br}

You can also use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form to disable individual features in Acumatica ERP. ((({S:Hint}We recommend that you ''not'' disable any feature after it has been enabled and used in the live system; this may cause unexpected results, including data loss.
)))
