If you use the user types functionality (for details, see [[#_775858a7-972a-4226-ac5d-7e74ae894419|User Types]) you can specify the following security settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_25_00|User Types] ([~/?ScreenId=EP202500|EP202500]) form that will be applied to all users of this type:[anchor|#_9fc1df49-697e-41fd-8806-da0d40d7fcbc] *Allow users with linked contacts to use their emails as their login to the system. *Force new users to change their password at the first login. *Force new users to activate their account.
