For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Site_Security_Options|Security Policies in Acumatica ERP]. ==Management of User Accounts== During ongoing maintenance of Acumatica ERP, you may have tasks to add a new user account or to change settings of an existing user account. You perform the following steps to configure a user account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form:[anchor|#_0c7c906e-f315-49b6-8794-972554b4046c] #You specify or change the login, password, user&rsquo;s first and last name, and email address. #Optional: You assign the user account the appropriate user type. For details, see [[#_775858a7-972a-4226-ac5d-7e74ae894419|User Types]. #Optional: You set up password policies for the user account. For details, see [[#_a4dc92fd-b47a-4ac1-8cf0-951188abd256|Security Policies for a User Account]. #You assign the user account the appropriate user roles. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Role-Based_Access|Role-Based Access].
For a detailed procedure of creating a user account, see [HelpRoot_Administration\US__how_Create_User_Account|To Create a Local User Account].{br}
If users of the system are using the Acumatica mobile app, the information about their devices that allow push notifications from the app is stored in their Acumatica ERP user profiles on the '''Devices''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form. When a user signs in to the mobile app for the first time, the application sends details about the device to Acumatica ERP, and then the information is updated with each subsequent sign-in. {br}
You can delete any device listed on this tab by clicking it and using the standard button on the table toolbar, or you can delete all devices for a user by clicking the '''Delete All''' button on this toolbar. Also, you can control to which devices the system can send push notifications. You can use the '''Turn On Notifications''' check box to selectively allow or disallow these notifications for devices. You can also enable or disable sending push notifications for all user&rsquo;s devices by clicking the '''Enable All''' and '''Disable All''' buttons, respectively, on the table toolbar. ==Location Tracking of Users== In Acumatica ERP, you can view the GPS location coordinates of users that are tracked through their mobile devices. To be able to view a user&rsquo;s coordinates in the system, you have to configure location tracking for each necessary user on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form. You use the '''Location Tracking''' tab to turn on the tracking functionality for the selected user, specify the time and distance intervals at which the coordinates will be tracked in the system, and specify on which days and during which time periods the system registers the user location. For detailed instructions on how to turn on and configure the location tracking, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__HOW_To_Turn_on_Location_Tracking|To Turn On Location Tracking of a User].((({S:Warn}For GPS location coordinates to be tracked, on the user&rsquo;s device, GPS location recording has to be switched on. ))) You can view the history of the location coordinates of all users that have been tracked in the system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_00|Location Tracking History] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202000|SM202000]) form.[anchor|#_775858a7-972a-4226-ac5d-7e74ae894419] ==User Types== Your company may need to give your partners limited access to Acumatica ERP—for instance, to facilitate the process of entering contacts or customer orders. In such a scenario, you may need some way to segregate users that are internal to your company from external users, or even to give your partners the means to create and manage their own users in Acumatica ERP, thus freeing your administrators of the responsibility to manage these users. You can address these requirements through the use of user types in Acumatica ERP.{br}
Each user type can be either employee-related or contact-related:[anchor|#_d3017f42-de9e-4007-ba83-9e79356bbd44] *An employee-related user type is associated with employees in your system. These user types are intended for users who are internal to your company (generally employees of your company and possibly consultants that you consider part of your company). *A contact-related user type is associated with a contact in your system. These user types are intended for users who are external to the company—for example, partners or contacts. As opposed to employee-related user types, you can use contact-related user types to delegate the right to create users, as described in [HelpRoot_Administration\US__how_Delegation_User_Creation_Rights|To Delegate the Right to Create Users].
For each user type, you need to specify the set of roles that can be assigned to users of this type. For the procedure to add a user type, see [HelpRoot_Administration\US__how_Add_Contact_User_Type|To Add a User Type]. ==Ability to Track User Accounts== You can use the following forms to track details on user accounts:[anchor|#_69492678-841d-4501-bfb2-9d0482d244ef] *Print or view a list of users in your Acumatica ERP instance by using the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SM_65_05_00|User List] ([~/?ScreenId=SM650500|SM650500]) report. *View the access rights for each user to any system objects (suites, modules, forms, and form elements) by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_55|Access Rights by User] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201055|SM201055]) form.
