Within Acumatica ERP, users can perform searches in help, wikis, and various ''entities'', such as vendors, customers, invoices, and contracts. To make the process quick and accurate, Acumatica ERP uses semantic search and search indexes. ==Semantic Search in Acumatica ERP== Acumatica ERP uses semantic search through SQL databases that allows the system to identify the key phrases in text or documents, discover similar or related documents, and provide information to explain how documents are similar or related.{br}
To employ semantic search in your Acumatica ERP instance, make sure that semantic search functionality is enabled in your SQL server. [anchor|#ul_qqk_15h_5r] *In Microsoft SQL Server, the semantic search functionality is disabled by default. Enable the functionality, as described in [HelpRoot_Install\how__Semantic_Search|Enabling Semantic Search for Microsoft SQL Server] in Acumatica ERP Installation Guide. *In MySQL Server, the semantic search functionality is enabled by default.
==Search Indexes== The search indexes are used to accelerate searching in Acumatica ERP. When users perform the day-to-day operations, such as adding new documents or updating customer accounts, the new information is added to the appropriate search indexes automatically. You need to rebuild the search indexes in the following cases: [anchor|#_14537503-d814-46c2-aa6e-b00eeb7e4218] *After you have upgraded your Acumatica ERP system from a version that did not include the search indexes *After you have installed an Acumatica ERP tenant with demo data
For detailed procedure, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__how_Search_indexes_update|To Build Search Indexes].{br}
The list of indexed entities, excluding the wikis, is available on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_95_00|Rebuild Full-Text Entity Index] ([~/?ScreenId=SM209500|SM209500]) form. {br}
The built-in help wikis are indexed automatically. The wikis created in your system are not indexes automatically; you must add search indexes for such wikis manually, as described [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__how_Wiki_Setting_Up_a_New_Wiki|To Add a Wiki]. Wiki search indexes are not displayed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_95_00|Rebuild Full-Text Entity Index] form. ==Known Limitations to Search Queries== A semantic search does not find related entities if the search query includes word breakers, such as <tt>AND</tt> or <tt>FOR</tt>.{br}
For example, suppose that you want to find related entities by using a description as a search query. The description includes at least one word breaker, so in this case, the search returns no results. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Administration\SM__mng_Search|Managing Search] *[HelpRoot_Interface\UIG__con_New_UI_Search|Search] *[HelpRoot_Administration\SM__how_Search_indexes_update|To Build Search Indexes]

 Acumatica ERP and the Acumatica mobile app provides mechanisms to support two-factor authentication to prevent unauthorized system access. Security-conscious businesses require two-factor authentication to verify user identities before allowing them to access sensitive ERP data.((({S:Warn}This functionality is available only if the ''Two-Factor Authentication'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form.
)))
Access is granted only after the user successfully presents to the system additional evidence of authentication in addition to the user&rsquo;s credentials (that is, the username and password). At the system level, a system administrator can require two-factor authentication or turn off this authentication (the default setting). In addition, the administrator can specify different settings for individual users with regard to two-factor authentication; user settings take precedence over system-wide settings.{br}

If two-factor authentication is required, the user needs to authenticate the sign-in operation by using one of the methods displayed in the following screenshot.[anchor|#_c0b67561-4712-4c43-ae6b-30f6ef26b09e][image:UserGuide/Images/2019R1_RN_TwoFactor_2.png|popup|250px]{br}

By default, when two-factor authentication is enabled, the system uses the push notification method to authenticate the login operation.((({S:Warn}Push notifications are available only for instances with a valid license.
))){br}

The push notification method of authentication requires the Acumatica app to be set up on a mobile device.[anchor|#_386f2e44-3f7d-4d17-8308-64932c38f53f][image:UserGuide/Images/2019R1_RN_TwoFactor_1.png|popup|250px]{br}

You can specify whether the user confirms authentication in one of the following ways:[anchor|#_9658494d-2d2f-472c-ab92-fe59f1e01c69]
*By tapping '''Approve''' in Acumatica mobile app push notification.
*By email. This authentication method will be on the the login screen list if the administrator selects the ''Allow Email'' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201060|SM201060]) form.
*Via SMS. This authentication method will be in on the the login screen list if the administrator selects the ''Allow SMS'' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] form.
*By generating codes in Acumatica mobile app with the '''Generate Access Code''' command.
*By generating codes on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) or User Profile (SM203010) form.
{br}

The '''Two-Factor Authentication Policy''' section on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] form is used for setting up system-wide two-factor authentication preferences. The settings in this sentence affect all of the company's users that do not have their own settings specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] form. 
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] form, in the '''Two-Factor Authentication''' section, the administrator must select the '''Override Security Preferences''' check box in order to override the system default settings and specify the two-factor authentication mode for a specific selected user. (Otherwise, the settings specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] form will be used.)
If two-factor authentication is required for a particular user, the first time that user signs in to the Acumatica mobile app, the system will request the security access code that will be sent to the user&rsquo;s email address when the user signs in to the web version of Acumatica ERP. The mobile app will also require PIN code or biometric verification when the user signs in. By invoking the '''Generate Access Code''' command in the account editing menu of the mobile app, the user can generate access codes for two-factor authentication.
