Acumatica ERP provides the functionality to monitor and manage three types of events:[anchor|#_af37e558-887c-423b-a81f-5dc22dcb0f58] *Events that are planned by people *Changes to system data *Schedule-based checking of conditions in the system
Acumatica ERP provides the ''event'' functionality and the ''business event'' functionality for the management and monitoring of events. ==Event Functionality== The event functionality is suitable for monitoring and managing events to be held by your company employees, customers, or vendors. Users can create these events—which can include meetings, seminars, trade shows, and conference calls—in the system. Acumatica ERP gives users the ability to send personalized emails to all participants based on notification templates that can be defined for inviting potential attendees to an event, rescheduling an event, and canceling an event. ((({S:Warn}Although it would be possible to monitor system data changes by using the event functionality, we do not recommend this. You instead use the business event functionality, which was developed specifically for this purpose. ))) ==Business Event Functionality== You use the business event functionality for monitoring business events that occur in the system as users perform business processes. Business events are particular actions, data changes, or conditions that require user attention in your company. By setting up business event monitoring, you ensure that these business events will not be missed without individual users needing to spend their time performing manual monitoring.{br}
You can configure Acumatica ERP not only to monitor for particular business events but also to perform any number of actions (such as sending an email notification or performing the instructions defined by an import scenario) in the system. The system performs these actions based on either of the following occurrences:[anchor|#_77bf784f-419b-495b-a74b-0628c9079fe0] *Specific data being changed in the system. *:For example, in contract management, you can configure the system to send an email notification to the customer when the customer&rsquo;s contract is activated. *The meeting of particular conditions, which the system checks for at the schedule you specify. *:For example, in the management of opportunities, you can configure the system to send an email to the owner of an opportunity when it is one month from its estimated close date and the opportunity hasn&rsquo;t been updated for more than seven days. The system performs this monitoring once a day. [anchor|#_e9e6364c-586a-4e74-88a5-a8cbf5d21dd0] To configure the system to monitor a business process, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form, you define a ''business event'' that relates to this business process and that causes the system to perform an action or multiple actions in the system. The business event is a data change or a set of conditions checked for on a schedule. For details on the business events, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_By_Data_Change|Business Events Related to Data Changes] and [HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_By_Schedule|Business Events Monitored on a Schedule]. To define the actions that the system should perform in the system once the business event has occurred, you specify the ''subscribers'' of this business event. A subscriber of a business event is an entity in the system (an email, a push notification to a mobile device, or a script based on an import scenario) that the system processes when the business event occurs. If the subscriber is an email or a push notification, the system sends the needed emails or push notifications based on the settings of the notification template that you have specified for the business event. If the subscriber is an import scenario, the system executes the sequence of instructions defined by the import scenario that you have specified for the business event. For more information about subscribers, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_Subscribers|Subscribers of Business Events]. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_e40a7408-8e91-40f5-9421-89e84f8554d4] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_bf2fc07b-8edf-4c07-b4fa-d0205d5ef182] *[HelpRoot_Administration\EP__con_Notifications_About_Events|Notifications About Events] *[HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Notifications_About_Changes|Notifications About Changes on Data Entry Forms] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_By_Data_Change|Business Events Related to Data Changes] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_By_Schedule|Business Events Monitored on a Schedule] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_Subscribers|Subscribers of Business Events]
| [anchor|#_390c217b-53c6-4e84-b117-ba15a1a805ed] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AI__how_Business_Event_by_Record_Change|To Monitor Changes of the Business Process Data] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AI__how_Business_Event_by_Schedule|To Monitor the Business Process Data by a Schedule]
