By using Acumatica ERP, you can configure automatic notifications about various events in the organization, such as training sessions, work meetings, conference calls, and trade shows. Users create events and invite leads, contacts, and customers to attend them, and the system sends invitations to the potential attendees specified for the event. Also, the system reminds users about the event and notifies attendees if you make any changes to the event or cancel it.{br}{TOC} ==Event-Related Settings== By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_70|Event Setup] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204070|EP204070]) form, you can configure automatic notifications about events to be held by your company employees. You can configure either simple (built-in) notifications or template-based notifications that allow users to send personalized emails. A template can include placeholders that are replaced by each addressee's personal data, such as the first and last names and position, when the system generates event notification emails.{br}
You can create the following templates: [anchor|#ul_u3r_jwy_w3] *''Invitation template'': This template can be used to send personalized email invitations to the persons listed on the '''Attendees''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_30|Event] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306030|CR306030]) form. If the user adds new potential attendees to the list after sending initial invitations and saves the event, the system will prompt the user to send invitations to the added potential attendees. *''Rescheduling template'': This template can be used if the event date or time has been changed. Emails based on the template are sent to all invited persons automatically once the event is shifted to a new start time. *''Cancellation template'': This template is used if the invitation to the event is canceled for a particular potential attendee (for instance, if the event planner sent the invitation to this person in error) or for all potential attendees.
==Creation of New Events== Users can view existing events by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404100|EP404100]) form. Clicking the '''Add Event''' button on the table toolbar invokes the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_30|Event] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306030|CR306030]) form (as a pop-up window), which lets you create a new event. {br}
When creating an event, the user may configure a ''reminder'' for it, specifying the day and time when all invited attendees will be reminded about the event (by the '''Automatic Reminder''' dialog box popping up). ==Event-Related Notification Emails== If a user creating an event specifies potential attendees, notification emails will be sent at the following times to the specified parties: [anchor|#ul_rz2_zht_w3] *When the event is being saved for the first time: To all potential attendees *When new attendees are added: To only newly added attendees *When the event is rescheduled: To all potential attendees *When the event is canceled: To all potential attendees *When the invitation is canceled: To the selected potential attendees
==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_70|Event Setup] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204070|EP204070])

In Acumatica ERP, you can configure record change notifications if the ''Change Notifications'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. Record change notifications are emails the system generates and sends when specific changes are made to particular documents.{br}{TOC} ==Uses of Record Change Notifications == Notifications can help your employees and selected external contacts track key developments that occur within the organization. Some examples include the following: *A sales manager may want the system to notify a customer contact when a sales order has been shipped to the customer. *Your company might want to tell customers about changes in their blanket purchase orders. *A manager may want to know when a specific purchase order has received all the required approvals. *A credit manager may want to know when a sales order is created for a particular customer that is approaching its credit limit. *A customer service manager may want to be informed when a new employee is assigned a case of a specific type, to give the employee assistance with this type of case.
==Public and Private Notifications== You can configure private notifications to be received by only particular recipients and public notifications for which users can sign up. {br}
For private notifications, you can specify very precise conditions for sending the notification email, and choose only appropriate individuals to receive it. {br}
You can configure public notifications about typical changes in documents of a specific type that employees and external contacts may want to know about. These public notifications are visible to all users who have access to the respective data entry forms. When a user is viewing a document of the specific type on the form, the user can sign up for the notification to receive emails about changes made to the particular document. ==Access to Notification Configuration== To create a new notification, a user should have access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] ([~/?ScreenId=SM205040|SM205040]) form at the ''Insert'' level of access or higher. {br}
If you want multiple users to be able to create new notifications, configure a ''Notification Administrator'' role with an ''Insert'' or ''Delete'' level of access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] form. Users with this role can then create private and public notifications for other users of the organization. {br}
A user doesn&rsquo;t need access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] form, however, to sign up for an existing public notification. If a user has access to a data entry form for which public notifications have been configured, the user can sign up for notifications associated with the form, to monitor changes in specific records or documents. ==Creation of a New Public Notification== To begin creating a new public notification about changes in documents of a specific type or certain records, do one of the following: *Open the form where specific documents are created, click '''Notifications''' (upper right of the form), and then click '''Create New'''. This opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] form as a pop-up window so that you can create a new notification. *Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] form directly, and select the data entry form of interest in the '''Screen ID''' box.
Now that you are on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] form with the appropriate screen selected, perform the following steps: #Provide a description for the notification. After you save the notification, the description will serve as the notification ID. #Make sure the '''Active''' check box is selected. #Provide a subject for emails to be sent for this notification. #Optional: In the '''Data Source''' box, select one of the following options: #*''Report'': To send an electronic version of the document with the notification email, either as an attachment or as the email body. If you select this option, specify the '''Report ID''', the '''Report Format''', and, optionally, report parameters on the '''Parameters''' tab (which appears after you have selected a report ID). To send the document in the email body, select the '''Embedded''' check box; in this case, you cannot specify other text for the email message. #*''Action'': To execute a specific action once a notification email is generated. For example, if you configure notification emails as emails based on an email template, by using this option, you can specify whether to print the document, release it, or void it. #*''None'': To not perform any additional actions. #Select the''' Public''' check box. #Click the '''Message''' tab. If you have selected the '''Embedded''' check box, the document generated based on the specified report will be used as email body; otherwise, type the text of the notification email, or paste the notification template that you previously created in the Notifications wiki. To make emails personalized, use placeholders in double parentheses, such as ''((EmployeeFirstName))''. #Do the following to specify the conditions that the system will check when the document is saved and send notification emails if the conditions are met: #*On the '''Conditions''' tab, specify the conditions for the document field values. #*On the '''Fields''' tab, select the fields whose changes should be monitored. #On the '''Addresses''' tab, specify the list of recipients. For each recipient, specify the following information: #*In the '''Source''' box, select one of the following options as the source of the recipient&rsquo;s address: ''Document'' (to select recipients among the contacts associated with the document, such as customer or vendor contacts) or ''User'' (to select recipients among all users defined in the system). #*In the '''Email''' box, select the email address of the recipient. #*Make sure the '''Active''' check box is selected. #*In the '''Type''' box, select the type of this recipient: ''To'', ''CC'', or ''BCC''. #Click '''Save'''.
==Signing Up for a Public Notification== Public notifications created for a particular data entry form are visible to all users who have access to the form. {br}
To sign up for a public notification, a user should do the following: #Open the data entry form, and select the appropriate document. #Click '''Notifications''' (upper right of the title bar). From the drop-down list of options, click the particular notification, which opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] form (a version of the form intended only for signing up) as a pop-up window. #On the '''Addresses''' tab, add the user&rsquo;s own email address to the list of recipients. #:((({S:Warn}On the '''Conditions''' tab of the pop-up window, a new line with the document reference number will be added automatically. ))) #Click '''Save'''.
After the user has completed these steps, if the values in the monitored elements are changed, the user will receive a notification email. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_40|Automation Notifications] ([~/?ScreenId=SM205040|SM205040]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_50|Send Notifications] ([~/?ScreenId=SM205050|SM205050]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_60|Send Reports] ([~/?ScreenId=SM205060|SM205060])

You can configure the system to perform actions when a change of the data related to a business process has occurred. In this topic, you can find information about the configuration and processing of the business events related to data changes.{br}{TOC} ==Business Event Configuration== To configure the system to perform actions related to data changes, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form, you create a business event of the ''Trigger by Record Change'' type and specify the following: [anchor|#_e4e402cd-e4bd-433d-a0a8-b16b7c643f47][anchor|#_78b12dad-74e8-4d65-8dca-63e5ee31d752] *The data for monitoring. *:In the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you can select an existing generic inquiry form or the generic inquiry form, which you have created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_80_00|Generic Inquiry] ([~/?ScreenId=SM208000|SM208000]) form, that defines the data for the system to monitor. You can also select a shared filter (if one has been defined for the form).((({S:Warn}Business events do not support generic inquiries that have grouping specified on the '''Grouping''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_80_00|Generic Inquiry] form. The generic inquiry that you use should be as simple as possible. Thus, we recommend that you avoid unnecessary multiple joins and joins to the same tables. In most cases, you can exclude from the generic inquiry all the tables that are not used on the '''Results Grid''' tab of the corresponding generic inquiry form. ))) *The conditions that must be met for the system to perform actions. *:On the '''Trigger Conditions''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you configure the conditions when the system should perform actions related to the business process. You can configure the conditions that are applied to any of the following:[anchor|#_b28880ac-077b-495e-8dfc-563493797c77] **The results of the generic inquiry before the data change (the old field values). **The results of the generic inquiry after the data has been changed (the new field values). **The comparison of these results. That is, the condition can check whether a field value has been changed, or a record has been added, removed, or updated.The action is performed if the inquiry results have been changed according to the specified conditions.[anchor|#_39e22f27-4d9c-4295-b999-2eb77f343edd] *The action or actions that the system should perform if the specified conditions have been met. *:On the '''Subscribers''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you select a subscriber that has been configured; if needed, you can select multiple subscribers (one in each row). To create a new subscriber, you click '''Create Subscriber''' and click the menu command corresponding to the type of the subscriber, which causes the system to open the Acumatica ERP form (for an email or a push notification to a mobile device) or the dialog box and form (for an import scenario script) to create the subscriber. For details about subscribers of both types, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AI__con_Business_Event_Subscribers|Subscribers of Business Events]. *:((({S:Warn}If you plan to send push notifications to users of the Acumatica mobile app on mobile devices, make sure that the generic inquiry you have selected (in the '''Screen Name''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form) includes the <tt>NoteID</tt> data field for the entity that you plan to display when a user taps a notification on the mobile device. For example, suppose that you want to notify employees about new opportunities assigned to them, and when an employee taps this notification, the app should display the new opportunity. In this case, you should add the <tt>NoteID</tt> data field for the object <tt>CROpportunity</tt> on the '''Results Grid''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_80_00|Generic Inquiry] ([~/?ScreenId=SM208000|SM208000]) form. ))) *:If you have specified multiple subscribers on the '''Subscribers''' tab for the business event, you can select the '''Stop on Error''' check box in the row of a subscriber to direct the system to process subsequent subscribers in the list only if no error has occurred while the system was processing the current subscriber. {br}
In the '''Raise Event''' box of the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you can also select how the system should generate the business event: for each record that satisfies the trigger conditions or for the whole set of records that satisfy the trigger conditions.{br}
For details on how to configure the system to monitor business events related to record changes, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AI__how_Business_Event_by_Record_Change|To Monitor Changes of the Business Process Data]. ==An Example of the Business Event Configuration== For example, suppose that you want to configure the system to send a notification to the customer when this customer&rsquo;s contract has been activated. You would do the following: [anchor|#_87be13bd-6790-4c4e-b6cb-eec7c285b496] #Optional: Create a generic inquiry (based on the <tt>PX.Objects.CT.Contract</tt> and <tt>PX.Objects.AR.ARContact</tt> tables) that retrieves from the system all contracts along with the applicable customer contact details. #:((({S:Warn}You could instead use an existing generic inquiry when you define the business event, if one exists that retrieves the needed data. We recommend that you check whether only the needed fields and tables are used in the generic inquiry you have decided to use. If the already-existing inquiry uses any fields and tables that are unnecessary for your specific business event, you should instead create a new inquiry and use it. ))) #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form, create a business event with the following settings: #*'''Type''': ''Trigger by Record Change'' #* '''Raise Event''': ''For Each Record'' (to make the system generate a business event for each activated contract) #*'''Screen Name''': The generic inquiry you have created #On the '''Trigger Conditions''' tab, add two rows with the following values: #*Row 1: #**'''Operation''': ''Field Changed'' #** '''Table Name''': ''Contract'' (<tt>PX.Objects.CT.Contract</tt> table) #**'''Field Name''': ''Status'' #** '''Operator''': And #*Row 2: #**'''Operation''': ''New Field Value'' #** '''Table Name''': ''Contract'' (<tt>PX.Objects.CT.Contract</tt> table) #**'''Field Name''': ''Status'' #** '''Condition''': ''Equals'' #** '''Value 1''': ''Active'' #On the '''Subscribers''' tab, select a notification template. For this example, you would create a notification template that specifies as the recipient of the email a placeholder that has the system extract the default email address of the customer contact specified in the activated contract.
==Business Event Processing== When a business event is configured and is active—that is, the '''Active''' check box is selected for it on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form—the system starts monitoring data changes made to the data included in the generic inquiry form. If a record has been changed, the system checks whether the record satisfies the conditions specified on the '''Trigger Conditions''' tab. If the record satisfies the conditions (which means that the business event has occurred), the system processes the subscribers of the event that are specified on the '''Subscribers''' tab. {br}
After all subscribers of the business event have been processed, the system saves information about the processing of the business event, which you can view on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_50_20_30|Business Event History] ([~/?ScreenId=SM502030|SM502030]) form.{br}
