You can configure the system to perform actions based on the occurrence of particular events, which the system checks for at the schedule you specify. In this topic, you can find information about the configuration and processing of this type of business events.{br}{TOC} ==Business Event Configuration== To configure the system to perform actions based on the occurrence of particular events, which the system checks for at the schedule you specify, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form, you create a business event of the ''Trigger by Schedule'' type and specify the following: [anchor|#_861d8622-f713-4f2a-875b-8e8ea6143e1b][anchor|#_78b12dad-74e8-4d65-8dca-63e5ee31d752] *The data for monitoring. *:In the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you can select an existing generic inquiry form or the generic inquiry form, which you have created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_80_00|Generic Inquiry] ([~/?ScreenId=SM208000|SM208000]) form, that defines the data for the system to monitor. *The conditions that must be met for the system to perform actions. *:On the '''Trigger Conditions''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you configure the conditions when the system should perform actions related to the business process. These conditions are based on the fields of the records of the generic inquiry. The actions are performed if the inquiry results satisfy the specified conditions.[anchor|#_75fa3de7-8493-4bab-a115-8900cecf69b7] *The action or actions that the system should perform if the specified conditions have been met. *:On the '''Subscribers''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] form, you select a subscriber that has been configured; if needed, you can select multiple subscribers (one in each row). To create a new subscriber, you click '''Create Subscriber''' and click the menu command corresponding to t