The user interface of Acumatica ERP provides predefined user interface elements, such as workspaces and workspace tiles and links, which you can configure to adjust the user interface to the business processes of your organization. Because the employees of your organization can locate the forms they use most right away, they can perform their working tasks related to Acumatica ERP more easily. {br}
For the description of the user interface elements, see [HelpRoot_Interface\UIG__con_New_UI| Acumatica ERP User Interface].{br}
In this topic, you will read about the capabilities in the system for customizing the user interface.{br}{TOC} ==User Role for the Customizing the User Interface== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201060|SM201060]) form in the '''Menu Editor Role''' box you can specify any available user role. A user with this role will be able to customize the user interface (in particular, main menu and workspace links) in the special Menu Editing mode. The changes made in this mode are applied to all users of Acumatica ERP. ((({S:Warn}We recommend creating a dedicated role and assign it to those users who should have access to the user interface modification. ))) ==Customization of the User Interface== You can customize the user interface as follows:[anchor|#_60b6fc42-9307-4431-a8e8-bb30a142e528] *Adjust the list of workspaces that are items on the main menu: You can keep in the user interface only the workspaces that correspond to the business processes of your organization. To perform this task, you can add new workspaces and populate them with items (tiles and links that provide access to forms and reports), delete existing menu items for workspaces that do not comply with your business processes, and rename existing workspaces. For details, see [[#_67fc05a9-d987-4260-93c5-fb47ecc8ea40|Management of the Workspaces Listed on the Main Menu]. *Change the items of a workspace: You can customize a workspace so that only the items that your employees use in their work are displayed there. You can change the list of forms, reports, and dashboards in a workspace, regroup the links to forms and reports in a workspace, reorder the links to forms and reports in a category, remove unnecessary tiles and links to forms, reports, and dashboards from a workspace, and reorder tiles in a workspace. For more information, see [[#_334a2f9f-1e24-42b1-a323-1dff1dd42040|Management of Workspace Tiles and Links].
By using Menu Editing mode, you can customize the user interface in a variety of ways. To switch to this mode, on the main menu, you click the configuration menu button ([anchor|#_55f9375f-7fbb-4a10-a2f2-cdbb78a3972d][image:UserGuide/Images/Main_Menu_Dots.png|25px]) and then click '''Edit Menu'''.{br}
If you customize the user interface in this mode and then decide to return the initial state of the main menu and all workspaces, you can reset the menu settings to default. Changes in the following menu elements will be reset: [anchor|#_2857f336-086f-46e8-934e-9315ddc8785c] *The list of workspaces that are items on the main menu and the '''More Items''' menu *Items in each workspace, including categories, tiles, and links to forms, reports, and dashboards *Items in quick menu of each workspace for all users of the system *Workspaces pinned to the main menu and unpinned from the main menu for all users of the system ((({S:Hint}If your changes are not applied immediately after refreshing the page, we recommend clearing browser cache and loading the page again. ))) For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Reset_Menu_Settings|To Reset Menu Settings].[anchor|#_67fc05a9-d987-4260-93c5-fb47ecc8ea40] ==Management of the Workspaces Listed on the Main Menu== The main menu is the primary navigation tool that you and the employees of your organization use when you start working in Acumatica ERP. The system provides you with predefined workspaces list that is displayed in the main menu. The list of workspaces that a user sees by default is determined by the features enabled based on your Acumatica ERP license and the access rights of the user roles assigned to the particular user account.((({S:Warn}You must configure access rights for users to each form and report that belongs to a workspace. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\US__con_Access_Rights|User Access Rights]. ))) If the default list of workspaces (that is, the items on the main menu) does not correspond to the business processes of your organization, you can configure the list as follows:[anchor|#_8aa21377-c78c-41aa-b793-7188779a49df] *Rename existing workspaces: If a title of any existing workspace is not optimal for your company&rsquo;s users, you can change the title to help users easily find the forms and reports they need. For the steps you need to perform to rename a workspace, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Rename_Workspace|To Rename a Workspace]. *Delete existing workspaces: If a predefined workspace does not fit the business processes of your organization and will not be needed by system users, you can completely delete it from the system. When you delete a workspace, the system completely deletes tiles that belonged to the workspace, but forms, reports, and dashboards that belonged to the workspace remain in the system; you can add to other workspaces links to these forms, reports, and dashboards. For the procedure that describes how to delete a workspace, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Delete_Workspace|To Delete a Workspace]. *Add new workspaces: If your organization has a specific business process that requires forms, reports, and dashboards from different functional areas to be gathered on one menu for employees&rsquo; convenience, you can create a custom workspace and pin it to the main menu panel. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Add_Configure_Workspace|To Add and Configure a Workspace]. [anchor|#_334a2f9f-1e24-42b1-a323-1dff1dd42040] ==Management of Workspace Tiles and Links== Workspaces are used in the system to organize links to forms, reports, and dashboards in a way that is convenient to users. By default, each workspace contains tiles (buttons that provide users with quick access to frequently used forms) and links to forms, reports, and dashboards grouped by categories (such as '''Profiles''', '''Reports''', and '''Preferences'''). Each organization has its own business processes and uses sets of Acumatica ERP forms, reports, and dashboards based on these processes.{br}
To make a workspace convenient for the employees of your organization, you can do the following:[anchor|#_ca8ce07c-2db6-4669-bf80-122b539f3ed4] *Change the default list of links to forms, reports, and dashboards displayed in a workspace: If you need different forms, reports, and dashboards to be displayed in a workspace, you can change the default list by showing the items that are hidden by default and hiding the items that are displayed by default. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Display_Hide_Forms_in_Workspace_Menu|To Display and Hide Forms in a Workspace]. *Add new links to forms, reports, and dashboards to a workspace: If a link to a form, report, and dashboard is not on a workspace by default but the employees of your organization want to have it in this workspace, you can add the required link to any Acumatica ERP form, report, or dashboard to the workspace. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Add_Form_to_Workspace_Menu|To Add a Link to a Workspace]. *:((({S:Warn}If a link to a form or report has not been added to any of workspaces, you cannot find this form or report by using the '''Search''' box on the top pane of the Acumatica ERP screen. ))) *Regroup links to forms, reports, and dashboards in a workspace: If the default grouping of links to forms, reports, and dashboards in a workspace is inconvenient for the employees of your organization, you can move these links to other existing categories, or create a category that fits the terminology used by your employees. Changes to grouping settings affect only the workspace in which they are changed. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Regroup_Items_In_Workspace_Menu|To Regroup Forms and Reports in a Workspace ]. *:((({S:Warn}If you need to move a link to an existing category, which is displayed in a workspace, in the Menu Editing mode, you can simply drag the link to the category. ))) *Reorder links to forms, reports, and dashboards in a category: In the Menu Editing mode, you can reorder links to forms, reports, and dashboards in a category by dragging each link to a necessary position. *Remove links to forms, reports, and dashboards from a workspace: If you are sure that users will not need a particular link to a form, report, or dashboard in a workspace, you can remove this link from the workspace. (The form, report, or dashboard will remain in the system.) For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Remove_Form_From_Workspace_Menu|To Remove a Form or Report from a Workspace ]. *Delete preconfigured tiles: If the employees of your organization do not use functions preconfigured in tiles, you can delete the tiles from a workspace to have more space in the workspace. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Delete_Tile_from_Workspace_Menu|To Delete a Tile from a Workspace ]. *:((({S:Hint}After you delete a tile, you will be able to restore it only when restoring menu settings to default. ))) *Reorder tiles in a workspace: In the Menu Editing mode, you can reorder tiles in a workspace by dragging each tile to a necessary position.
==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Interface\UIG__con_New_UI| Acumatica ERP User Interface] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Add_Configure_Workspace|To Add and Configure a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Add_Form_to_Workspace_Menu|To Add a Link to a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Delete_Tile_from_Workspace_Menu|To Delete a Tile from a Workspace ] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Delete_Workspace|To Delete a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Display_Hide_Forms_in_Workspace_Menu|To Display and Hide Forms in a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Regroup_Items_In_Workspace_Menu|To Regroup Forms and Reports in a Workspace ] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Remove_Form_From_Workspace_Menu|To Remove a Form or Report from a Workspace ] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Rename_Workspace|To Rename a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_Administration\AS__how_Reset_Menu_Settings|To Reset Menu Settings]

Some companies may want to customize the Acumatica ERP interface style—that is, the look and feel of the user interface—to make it better fit their professional image. One facet of the interface style is the theme of the user interface: the color selections of different parts of the screen. An administrative user can select one of the predefined themes or a custom theme created for the company. The theme represents the package of the files that work together to determine the appearance of the system. {br}
In addition to changing the theme of the user interface, an administrative user can change the logo of each specific branch and the images displayed on the Sign-In page.{br}{TOC} ==Changing the Theme Used in the System== In Acumatica ERP, an administrative users that has access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_05|Site Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) form can change the theme of the interface the company uses. The theme is selected in the '''Interface Theme''' box of the '''General Defaults''' section. There are two predefined themes available in the system:[anchor|#_231a32ef-ed05-434f-9bbe-29d8e888ae79] *''Default'': This theme, which is applied by default, consists primarily of warmer blue, light gray, and white colors. *''Indigo'': This theme consists primarily of cooler blue, cold gray, and white colors.
You can select the name of a custom theme in this box, if one has been created. (The next section describes the creation process.){br}
When you select the ''Default'' theme on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_05|Site Preferences] form, the '''Primary Color''' box appears under the '''Interface Theme''' box. You can leave the default color defined in the theme or select a different primary color to be used for the user interface. For multibranch companies, a different color can be specified for each branch to make it easier for employees to distinguish between these branches.((({S:Warn}You can reset the changed primary color to the default color by clicking the '''Reset to Default Colors''' button next to the '''Interface Theme''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_05|Site Preferences] form. The system will reset the primary color for all companies and branches. ))) You change the color palette of the user interface by using the '''Primary Color''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_05|Site Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) form. The selected color palette is applied to all companies and branches, unless in the settings of a specific company or branch, the ability to override the site color is enabled and another color is selected. To change the color for a specific company or a branch, you do the following:[anchor|#_f105bc57-c4f2-4382-9fb0-9cf896a65cc7] *For a company: On the '''Theme''' section of the '''Visual Appearance''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_15_00|Companies] ([~/?ScreenId=CS101500|CS101500]) form, you first select the '''Override Colors for the Selected Company''' check box, and then select the needed color in the '''Primary Color''' box or specify the hexadecimal number of the color in the box next to the '''Primary Color''' box. *For a branch: On the '''Theme''' section of the '''Visual Appearance''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_20_00|Branches] ([~/?ScreenId=CS102000|CS102000]) form, you first select the '''Override Colors for the Selected Branch''' check box, and then select the needed color in the '''Primary Color''' box or specify the hexadecimal number of the color in the box next to the '''Primary Color''' box.
If a company has multiple branches, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_15_00|Companies] or the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_20_00|Branches] ([~/?ScreenId=CS102000|CS102000]) form to select the needed color. The color palette selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_15_00|Companies] form for the company with multiple branches is applied to all branches of a company unless in the settings of a specific branch, an override of the site color is enabled and another color is selected. ==Creating a Custom Theme== Users that have administrative access to the site database that is located on the server can edit the existing themes or create their own to apply them in the system. All themes are saved in the <tt>App&#95;Themes</tt> folder on the path that was specified for the site while the product was installed. When you insert a new folder into the <tt>App&#95;Themes</tt> folder, Acumatica ERP detects this folder and displays its name (which is also the name of the theme) in the list of the themes in the '''Interface Theme''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_05|Site Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) form. We highly recommend that you create new themes rather than edit the existing ones to avoid issues with the look and feel of the site. {br}
The following two files define the look and feel of the Acumatica ERP site:[anchor|#_50311acb-19a2-4564-9ee3-9e71cb913f35] *<tt>00&#95;Controls.css</tt>: Defines the formatting of the forms that appear on the UI. This file can be found through the following path: <tt>C:\Program Files\Acumatica ERP\MySite\App&#95;Themes\ThemeName</tt>. *<tt>Site.css</tt>: Defines the formatting of the navigation panels, tooltips, headers, and footers of the UI. This file can be found through the following path: <tt>C:\Program Files\Acumatica ERP\MySite\Content</tt>.
To create a custom theme, you copy the folder with the existing theme, insert it into the <tt>App&#95;Themes</tt> folder, and rename the copied folder to <tt>MyTheme</tt>, where ''MyTheme'' is the name you want to use for the theme being created. Then you copy the <tt>Site.css</tt> file and rename it to <tt>SiteMyTheme.css</tt>, where ''MyTheme'' is replaced by the name you want to use for the theme you are creating. To modify the look and feel of the forms, change the color scheme in the <tt>00&#95;Controls.css</tt> file of the folder that has the name of your theme, and save the changes. To modify the look and feel of the other elements of the UI, change the color scheme in the <tt>SiteMyTheme.css</tt> file (where ''MyTheme'' is the name you want to use for the theme being created) and save the changes. {br}
For instance, if you want to name your new theme ''Green'', you copy the <tt>Default</tt> theme folder and rename it to <tt>Green</tt>. Then you copy the <tt>Site.css</tt> file and you rename it to <tt>SiteGreen.css</tt> so that the system can detect that they are interconnected. {br}
When all files have been configured, you can select the created theme in the '''Interface Theme''' box of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_05|Site Preferences] form to apply the changes. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\CS__how_To_Change_Default_Theme|To Change the Default Theme of Acumatica ERP]. ==Changing the Company Logo== A company logo is a unique graphical symbol of the company that makes this company recognizable among others. Administrative users can change the site logo by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_15_00|Companies] ([~/?ScreenId=CS101500|CS101500]) form (for companies of the ''Without Branches'' type) and the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_20_00|Branches] ([~/?ScreenId=CS102000|CS102000]) form (for companies of the ''With Branches Not Requiring Balancing'' and ''With Branches Requiring Balancing'' type), on the '''Logo''' tab of both forms. The recommended size of the uploaded image is 210 by 50 pixels. ==Changing the Images on the Sign-In Page== Users that have administrative access to the site database that is located on the server can also customize the images displayed on the left side of the Sign-In page. The system displays a custom image from a set of images stored in the <tt>Icons</tt> folder (from <tt>login&#95;bg1.jpg</tt> to <tt>login&#95;bg9.jpg</tt>) on the path that was specified for the site while the product was installed. We recommend that you save the images that you will use for the Sign-In page with the same names as the original images have and that you reserve the original images for future use by changing the extension of these files from <tt>.jpg</tt> to <tt>.bak</tt>. The recommended size of each image is 1500 by 1000 pixels.[anchor|#_c372ac2e-893a-4fda-b037-be51ed038b7c] ==Inspecting Elements of the Webpage== While creating a custom theme, a user may wonder how to find the selector that is responsible for the formatting of a specific user interface element. Each browser has a set of web development and debugging tools called Developer Tools. These Developer Tools display the document object model (DOM) of the webpage or the DOM of a separate element on that page. On the '''Elements''' tab of the Developer Tools, the user can find the name of the source file where the code of the element is specified and the line of this code.{br}
On the needed page, a user can press F12 to open the '''Developer Tools''' window. To view the node for a specific element, the user can click the '''Select Element''' tool button (''Microsoft Internet Explorer'') on the '''Command Menu''' bar of the '''Developer Tools''' window and select that specific element on the webpage. The HTML node of the selected element appears on the '''Elements''' tab of the '''Developer Tools''' window. The CSS code of the selected element is displayed on the '''Styles''' tab on the right side of the same window. The following screenshot shows how the system displays the HTML and CSS code of the selected element.[anchor|#_8b01e94c-593a-4c36-a19e-092ee69252c1][image:UserGuide/Images/SourceCode.jpg|popup|600px] The following table displays the list of browsers and the name of the tool for each particular browser.[anchor|#_afc19e8c-272b-487c-9ef3-af3d4414ff04] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="50%" ! Browser !width="50%" ! Tool Name |- | Microsoft Internet Explorer | '''Select Element''' |- | Microsoft Edge | '''Select Element''' |- | Mozilla Firefox | '''Select Element by Click''' |- | Apple Safari | '''Start Element Selection''' |- | Google Chrome | '''Select an element in the page to inspect it''' |} Each <tt>.CSS</tt> file has commented lines that indicate the name of the class defined below these lines. You can use these lines to easily find the needed node through the document. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Administration\CS__how_To_Change_Default_Theme|To Change the Default Theme of Acumatica ERP]

