'''If your site is completely non-responsive or extremely slow:'''[anchor|#_f7db2fe3-bd91-48da-866c-72e97bfa2e46] #Create a dump file as follows: ##In Task Manager on the application server, find the <tt>w3wp.exe</tt> process that is run under the username that is the name of the application pool. ##Right-click on the process, and select '''Create Dump File''', as shown in the following screenshot. [anchor|#_3c1c0f93-6abf-4f3b-bc3e-4da2535a8ae5][image:UserGuide/Images/CreateDumpFile.png|popup|Creation of a dump file|250px] #:((({S:Warn}A process dump is a snapshot of an application showing what processes were executing and which modules were loaded at the time it was taken. The dump must be created only when the site is completely non-responsive or extremely slow. While you are creating a dump file, the process goes into a suspended mode, which will disconnect users from the site and lose any unsaved work. ))) #Provide the dump file to the Acumatica support team, along with other materials related to the performance slowdown issue. (For the list of information that you should provide to support, see [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step6|Step 6: Submit a Case to Acumatica Support].) [anchor|#_ca9df984-b2b3-4164-bb95-3345b6a45c45]{br}
'''If you need to track a randomly reproducible error'''[anchor|#_6a552e8b-d1ca-4293-8235-d48702eba7b5] #Enable the first-chance exception log as follows: ##Ensure that there is enough hard drive space on the Acumatica ERP installation drive (which by default is drive ''C)''. ##:((({S:Warn}The first-chance exception log grows quite quickly in size and should be enabled for only short periods of time. ))) ##In the <tt>web.config</tt> file in the Acumatica ERP site folder, find the ''EnableFirstChanceExceptionsLogging'' key, and change its value to ''true'', as shown in the following screenshot. [anchor|#_ae36c0ef-4e27-48b0-8c61-756723fed3df][image:UserGuide/Images/WebConfig.png|popup|Fragment of web.config|400px] ##Reproduce the problem. ##Find the first-chance exception log file in the site folder. By default, it is <tt>C:\Program Files (x86)\Acumatica ERP\&lt;Site Folder&gt;\firstchanceexceptions.log</tt>. #:((({S:Warn}The first-chance exception log is a powerful mechanism to track all exceptions in the system, but especially randomly reproducible errors. The difference between the first-chance exception log and the exception log that you can obtain by using the Request Profiler in Acumatica ERP (if you select '''Log Trace Messages''', '''Log Exceptions''', or both on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_70|Request Profiler] ([~/?ScreenId=SM205070|SM205070]) form) is that the first-chance exception log tracks not only committed transactions but also transactions that resulted in errors. ))) #Provide the first-chance exception log file to the Acumatica support team, along with other materials related to the performance slowdown issue. (For the list of information that you should provide to support, see [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step6|Step 6: Submit a Case to Acumatica Support].) [anchor|#_991d93b5-7072-411d-afec-6d666b7ef042] ==3. Use External Tools== You can use different external tools to get more information about the reasons for the performance slowdown.{br}
For example, you can use the [https://www.jetbrains.com/profiler/download/|dotTrace] performance profiler to create a process snapshot. If you use external tools to investigate performance issues, include the information obtained from these tools when you contact the Acumatica support team. (For the list of information that you should provide to support, see [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step6|Step 6: Submit a Case to Acumatica Support].)

 Acumatica ERP stores logs in a number of files and database tables. This topic contains information about the following logs:[anchor|#_2c65af12-468a-40db-82e4-67ffef9a637e]
*[[#_deeb5bf5-29da-4ff5-8ba1-5ae7c43c578b|Trace]: You can use this standard Acumatica ERP log for browsing issues that occur in the application.
*[[#_7462e6fa-d30a-4d53-a65b-364d128602ea|First-chance exception log]: This mechanism for catching and logging exceptions can be very helpful when you are facing a problem of an unknown origin.
*[[#_8e4da825-a68e-454f-bccd-7bc584e54a8a|Configuration Wizard logs]: These logs provide information related to issues occurring in the Acumatica ERP Configuration                             Wizard or Acumatica Framework                             Configuration Wizard.
*[[#_9edb70eb-081b-4dfa-a76c-2f2b5a5e7369|Maintenance logs]: In these logs, you can find details about issues that occur when you perform an upgrade in the Acumatica ERP application.
*[[#_ef13e9bd-7636-4652-a09c-b71a55248dee| Acumatica ERP logs]: These logs, which are stored in database tables, provide historical data for various operations.
*[[#_410a0c0d-7bbc-4da7-a712-83fcd301e54f|Windows logs]: These logs provide details for issues related to ASP.NET (for example, frequent application restarts or unhandled exceptions).
*[[#_a6164d1e-757c-485b-b8b4-1d0aef352c2e|IIS logs]: In these logs, IIS keeps records of all requests.
*[[#_b43e5bb8-85cf-4e40-8df1-fdb904ac4246|SQL Server logs]: These logs, kept by SQL Server, contain details for issues related to database accessibility and server maintenance operations.
